!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! SHORT DESCRIPTION (<<spoiler alert!>>)(If you have time and want to read the detailed description skip this part)Los Grillos Hermanos is a startup of the Food & Beverage industry. We will be producing massive quantities of hyper-proteic edible cricket powder, which has a competitive advantage in terms of price/protein content ratio respect to meat. Our mission is to feed human beings that are in a state of poverty with cricket powder, our vision is that animal protein market around the globe will see an increase in the demand in the next future, but it can not avoid to consider the environmental emergency, so it will convert some of the supply into a green source like insect. !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!      What is Los Grillos Hermanos.Before being a project of business and an opportunity to enter in a new market at the moment of its deregulation, Los Grillos Hermanos is the idea of using a raw edible material by exploiting at best its properties. Do you know that everyday 10 thousands kids die in Africa because of malnutrition? And do you know that this malnutrition is mainly caused by diets poor in protein consumption? (Source: FAO) We want to make our contribution in this struggle by massively producing cricket powder, a superfood that contains 60% of protein and several other crucial nourishments.  What are the benefit for their health, if malnutrished people start consuming insect proteins. We already mentioned that 3.6 million kids die for malnutrition every year only in Africa and more than 30 million people worldwide. Having state that, we are admitting that there exist a market for protein that does not fulfill its purpose: allocating efficiently its resources. The reason of this failure is simple: animal proteins have a huge cost for extremely poor people. By studying the production of cricket powder, a flour made by grinding dry crickets, we realized that we could offer the product for 4 €/kg in Third World Countries. Then we wanted to compare the price of our product with the one of our competitors, but we wanted to include in the reasoning not only the price but also the protein content, hence we decided to valuate by comparing the price of protein per kilogram. Meat in Africa has a price for protein content ratio of 35 €/kg, while cricket power's is 6.6 €/kg, which means that meat proteins costs 5-6 times more than cricket proteins.[proteins in : a) meat: 20%, b)crickets: 60%; price per kg: a) meat: 7€/kg, b)crickets: 4€/kg; price for a kg of protein: a) meat: 35 €/kg, b)crickets: 6.6 €/kg]The conclusion is self-evident, if you live in a Third world country and you are extremely poor, so poor that you cannot buy enough meat or fish to survive, you should try to buy insect protein, because beef proteins are more than five times expensive.If you are in a state of absolute poverty, you should consider to consume insects not only for their proteins, but also for other several reasons:

Calories: 100g of insects contains 120 kcal roughly. You should know that the second main cause of malnutrion diseases is the lack of calories. Since cricket powder must be mixed with wheat powder in equal parts to get pasta or bakery products, the consumption of cricket powder is always positively correlated with the consumption of calories.

Vitamines: insects contain fundamental vitamines, such as B12, which is the missing element in veagan diets, that only animal consumption can offer. Among the many vitamines, the most concentrated are vitamines A, B1, B2, B12 and E.

Acid fats: insects contain Omega 3 and Omega 6, two fundamental nourishments for the healthy growth of a child, that is normally assumed through blue fish. Often, landlocked countries have problems in integrating their diets with these two acid fats. Insects may be a nice way to get around the problem with a costless and natural solution.

High quality amminoacides: relatively to proteins it is also important to consider the quality of amminoacides: insects contain high quality amminoacides, fundamentals for the muscolar growth. These nourishments are not contained in vegetable proteins, such as beans or soy.
  What are the benefit for the environment if more and more people start converting their animal protein consumption towards insects.  The agribusiness is the second world polluter. Meat and fish markets are responsible for 24% of global emissions. This is mainly due to the fact that cows’ farts contain methan, which pollutes 25 times more than CO2. Since we raised cows population to billions, it became an issue. Agribusinesses pollutes also indirectly: 70% of agricultural land is used to produce vegetable proteins to feed animals. Since humans are globally increasing agricultural lands, partly by cutting down rainforests, reducing their lung breathing effect, we are deforesting to feed animals that will keep polluting. As everyone knows, if humans does not invert the pollution trend, consequences may be catastrophic. Insects may contribute to change things. Since 2003, the Food and Agricultural Organization, a UN agency, talks about environmental benefits in producing insects for human consumption. Insects are source of food incredibly more sustainable than traditional animal sources, crickets emit thousands times less Green House Gasses , they need 6 times less food to convert in edible product and they consume 4 times less water than cattles.As world population grows, we will need to produce more and more proteins, but we clearly cannot afford to keep using polluting sources such as cattle, pork and fish. If insects start integrating human diet in an increasing proportion, we may be able to decrease the damage we are inflicting to our own Planet to feed our vast population. What are our products?Our project purpose is to raise large cricket’s farms. These facilities can sell cricket powder, as already mentioned, dry crickets, alive crickets, mainly to be fed to reptiles, cricket poo, which is a sustainable and high-quality fertilizer, methan produced by the fermentation of cricket poo and all the derivative products that can obtained (pasta, bread, crackers, protein bars, snacks,...).  What can be cooked with cricket powder?Cricket powder should be considered equivalent to wheat flour, in an organic sense, and to meat and fish in the capacity of feeding a human being.It can be transformed in bread, pasta, cakes, milk shakes, juices and several other things.As an Italian company we believe that a natural outlet of cricket powder will be pasta. Cricket’s pasta is a perfect way to have a healthy meal if your economic resources are scarce and your struggling to buy meat and fish for your family: if you eat pasta with a vegetable sauce, such as tomato sauce, you are consuming high-quality proteins, vegetables, a fair quantity of carbohydrates, several important vitamins and acid fats. In our website there will be a dedicated section about recipes. We will hire a chef to shoot videos that will show how to cook cricket’s powder, that will be uploaded also on our Youtube channel. Who will be our customers?In developed countries we will have two main kind of target consumers for the cricket powder:People that care about sustainability of food: this people will consume our product because they believe in the cause of reducing the pollution emitted by our meals by choosing wisely what we eat. We will be able to reach this cluster selling to bio-shops, bio-supermarket, pharmacies and herbalists. In addition we will try to sell directly to retail customers through our website and our social media activities.People involved in fitness: if you care about your body and you want to consume less carbohydrates and more high-quality proteins, you should start considering eating cricket’s powder based meals. We will be able to reach this cluster selling to fitness shops, supermarkets, energy snack producers, food integrators producers, and gyms. In addition we will try to sell directly to retail customers through our website and our social media activities.On the contrary, in the Third world we will need to sell to entities that feed people that are in a poverty state: human organizations, schools, churches, soup kitchens, local governments or orphanages.Another type of customer, that will be extremely important in the beginning of operations, will be reptile breeders. Reptiles, as some fishes and frogs, require to eat alive crickets. We will be able to deliver alive crickets in Italy and some other close countries, such as Switzerland, France, Austria, Germany and Slovenia. Currently, people can buy alive crickets from their local pet shop or by online shops, in both cases the majority of those crickets will come from Eastern European farms. Hence, the animals are suffering at least 24 hours long travels before getting to the reptile breeder, resulting in high mortality rates. Our purpose is to supply Italian pet shops with periodical deliveries of italian alive crickets for a competitive price. Touching the market with first hand we realized that is very easy to convince pet shop to change their supplier if they  know that your facility is close, because the advantage in travel times, hence in mortality rates, is clear.Whole dry crickets will be an option in buying cricket powder and they are basically the ungrinded version of cricket powder. This product will be sold to exotic restaurants mainly, so they can actually show the cricket in their dishes, like in fried crickets.Hydrogen, Methan and zero km fertilizer: crickets will produce tons of waste product, which is composed by poo and exosckeletons mainly. We will wet this product and we will ferment it to obtain methan bubbles, that will be gathered in methan clynders. The resulting fermentated waste will be then dried to obtain a high quality agricultural fertilizer. Then methan (CH4) will be chemically processed to isolate hydrogen from carbon.  What are our short-term targets? This idea of business is very young in age, the study has began in August 2020 and it has been proposed to only two investors of capital, that immediately agreed on funding. Other two operating but still funding partners will join the business from January, taking care of biology, chemistry, humanitarian contacts, recruiting, legal and sales. Cash will flow to Los Grillos Hermanos from December 2020 and operations will officially begin in January 2021. To start operation in January and fund properly a digital marketing agency contract we agreed on asking to the community of Indiegogo 8000€.Our original will was to start operations in Siena, so that we could also link our production to very ancient and famous local products of our hometown. We have tried for weeks to find a warehouse nearby Siena, but no opportunity was offered by local real estate market.The closest appropriate facility we could find was in Certaldo (Firenze), a perfect spot to grow crickets, even if it is someway far from distribution centers.Then we received concerns about the legal italian situation for commerce, so we decided to change everything and start producing in UK, in Birmingham, which is the second british city by population, and it is widely more affordable then London. Right now we are taking into consideration the offer of one of our investor partner to produce in one of his warehouse in Milano. We are deepening legal situation to take the right choice... Assuming that we would be able to start operation in January in Milano, our short term targets will be: 
Open losgrilloshermanos.com by January 2021;
Build a greenhouse inside a warehouse to breed cricekets by February 2021;
Breed crickets, hence harvesting first batches of crickets from April 2021;
Create a Youtube channel with our initiatives, like the live stream of our live zoo, the recipes of the Chef, our video material, ... by January 2021;
Begin the partnership with a digital marketing agency from January 2021;
Start selling pasta and other derivatives of the cricket powder from June 2021;
Create a network of commercial agents with a coworking office in the warehouse from February 2021;
Start producing methan and hydrogen from June 2021;
Open Los Grillos Hermanos Foundation from January 2021;
...
 Our short-term goals will be:
Sell to 50 pet shops in Italy a 1000 alive crickets box every two weeks. This mean we will be selling for 2000€ every month.
Sell 100 kg of cricket powder every month at an average price of 10€/kg, which will generate selling for 1000 €.
 What is Los Grillos Hermanos Foundation? Another feature of our website will be the donation section, where people will be able to do charity: we will select 5 charitable projects around the globe to whom donate supplies of cricket powder. We will create an independent no-profit organization named Los Grillos Hermanos Foundation that will raise money for feeding people in some Third World Country facilities with cricket’s powder. This entity will operate separately from the Italian firm, but will buy from it the powder at a convenient and locked price. Donators will be found by using proper social media campaigns. Los Grillos Hermanos Foundation will try to raise specific crowdfunding campaigns such as in the following example. Suppose that there is a massive famine in East Africa, which strongly hit Addis Abeba, a huge city of 5 million people. LGHF may identify a poor neighbourhood of the suburbs of Addis Abeba, populated by 100 thousands people; it will have to make the computation and then ask donations for feeding this specific suburb with cricket protein for a certain period, like “Feed Suburb X of Addis Abeba, heavily hit by famine, for 3 months with cricket proteins”. This campaign could be a large charity crowdfunding that may be sustained by large companies, hence it can ask for millions. Specifically, this campaign would need to raise money to buy 900 tons of cricket powder, so it will have to raise 2-3 millions of euros. How we will reward your donation Your donation will be rewarded with our merchandise, with a periodical supply of alive crickets or with cricket powder.In case you choose to get rewarded with cricket powder we give you the chance to donate the product to our no-profit organization to be shipped to Third world needing facilities. By doing this, you will donate twice, once to a young social responsible business and once to needing people.Otherwise, you can donate a simbolic amount to be rewarded with our colourfull merchandising:
Shirts: here you can see unisex models but we can deliver you also the shirt for girls. Colours are yellow, white+yellow, white+red, red, light blue.
Hat: available only yellow for the moment:Apron: available only in yellow for the moment:Facemask: available in yellow and in white:  How would we use extra-donations:
We can fund a research project on artificial selection of crickets, in order to raise a healthier, bigger and fast-growing animal.
We may fund a nutritional and economic research on the impact of large use of insect protein in poor populations.
We will be able to fund an automation research in which we will try to build a system of breeding containers that gets their food and water supply from a machine that moves on a binary.
We will donate part of the sum to the no-profit organization, in order to fund a contract with a digital marketing agency.
We will fund the purchase of an industrial machine and all the relative equipment for pasta production, in order to experiment some format and maybe start selling.
 What can you do to support usYou can donate, but you can also do something even more important: you can share the cause of converting part of your protein consumption into insects, for the environment. Share this information to your contacts and we will be already glad for your help, news and description are on our social media pages. QUOTES: "the idea of using a raw edible material by exploiting at best its properties""3.6 million kids die for malnutrition every year""reducing the pollution emitted by our meals by choosing wisely what we eat""share the cause of converting part of your protein consumption into insects""Our mission is to feed human beings that are in a state of poverty with cricket powder"
